div#contact-info-step
  // same outer wrapper & class names as Guardrails
  div.buckets-guide-container
    // ───────── Title & intro ─────────
    h2 📄 Get Your Spreadsheet Ready
    p Before importing your <strong>Contact</strong> data, make sure your spreadsheet includes the following columns (✅ required / ⚙️ optional). Please note that additional fields are also available during the mapping process:

    // ───────── Checklist ─────────
    ol.guide-steps
      li
        span.step-icon 1️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Household ID (✅)
          |  – uniquely identifies a household.
      li
        span.step-icon 2️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Client ID (✅)
          |  – uniquely identifies the client.
      li
        span.step-icon 3️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Client Name (✅)
          |  – use
          code lastName, firstName
          |  format (e.g. Doe, John).


    // ───────── Best‑practice tips ─────────
    p.mt-3
      | • Keep Household / Client IDs consistent for future uploads.  
      br
      | • Source data from any CRM, or start with our template below.

    // ───────── Download + Learn‑More links ─────────
    a.import-action-item.d-block.mt-2(href='/downloads/contact-import-template.xlsx' download)
      i.fas.fa-file-download.me-1
      | Download the Contact Import template
    a.import-action-item.learn-more-btn.d-block.mt-2(      
      href='#'
      data-video-id='76979871'                           
      data-bs-toggle='modal'
      data-bs-target='#learnMoreVideoModal'
    )
      i.fas.fa-play-circle.me-1
      | Watch an instructional video (2 min)
    

    // ───────── Example header row (optional) ─────────
    .example-header.mt-4
      h4 🧪 Example Header Row:
      code Household ID | Client ID | Client Name | Marginal Tax Bracket % | Lead Advisor | Occupation | Retirement Date | Job Employer | Email | Phone Number | Deceased Living